; ADP process rules â€” agent wire format v1.1
; Comments ; â€” Fields KEY=val or KEY val
; Reference syntax: @path  @path#anchor  @path:Ln-Lm

v 1.1

flow PLANâ†’PROGRESSâ†’TESTâ†’DOCâ†’COMMIT
states NEW IN_PROG REVIEW DONE BLOCKED CANCEL DEFER
prio P0 P1 P2 P3

commit
 stage exact-path
 ban  -A . -a
 pre  git-status-short  ; verify staged
 post branch-contains   ; verify hash not orphan
 reset no-hard-without-stash
 hook fix=new-commit not=amend

bug
 gate0 git-pull restart-local-stack
 gates per-bug numbered
 close not-a-bug if gate0-fixes

session
 cap 70% util
 reread @dispatch.wire on=task-end
 endrit hashes done-ids stop ; no chat handoff

archive
 full  @../docs/tasks/archive/YYYY-MM-DD-tN-slug.md
 stub  5-8L in @../docs/tasks/current.md
 limit 800L active
 lookup index-rowâ†’grepâ†’chunkâ†’full ; default-deny full read

dispatch
 own arch
 update on=state-change
 read on=startup on=task-end
 size 3-5 tasks-per-role

lanes
 arch @../docs/{plans,prompts,tasks}/ @../memory/
 dev  see roles.wire
 des  see roles.wire
 rev  result-block-only

skills
 levels 1=frontmatter 2=skill-md-â‰¤5k 3=refs+scripts-on-demand
 trigger DO-list + NOT-list + keyword-examples
 inherit subagent â‰  parent  ; must declare

model
 arch opus    own architecture-design
 dev  sonnet  own implementation
 des  sonnet  own ui
 rev  haiku   own verify-only
 default subagent inherits ; pin explicit or pay opus rates

handoff
 medium files-on-disk ; never chat
 atom one-task-per-commit
 msg-format conventional ; <type>: <desc> (T{N})
